      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Involved in the restart of stalled replication forks, which reloads the replicative helicase on sites other than the origin of replication. Can function in multiple replication restart pathways. Displaces ssDNA from a PriB-ssDNA complex. Probably forms a spiral filament on ssDNA"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the DnaT family"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Homooligomerizes. Interacts with PriB. Component of the replication restart primosome. Primosome assembly occurs via a 'hand-off' mechanism. PriA binds to replication forks, subsequently PriB then DnaT bind; DnaT then displaces ssDNA to generate the helicase loading substrate"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
